name: Android App Development Integrating Firebase

venue.name: University of Texas at El Paso: Chemistry and Computer Science Building

description:
We will host a workshop that teaches beginner Android App Development and integrating with Google Cloud's Firebase services. The event will be divided up into 2 parts. The first being a beginners crash course into Android Development on Android Studio. The latter will consist of how to integrate Firebase into Android.

Please bring a laptop with Android Studio downloaded and ready to go!

The event will be hosted at the University of Texas at El Paso in the Chemistry and Computer Science Building in room[masked].

We hope to see everyone there!!!

name: Intro to Android Programming
description: This workshop will be the first of a series of workshops teaching Andoid Programming to complete beginners. The only pre-requisite knowledge we ask you to have is a basic understanding of object-oriented programming in Java. This workshop will be hosted by GDG's very own Edward Herrera who currently serves as a developer for a very popular local startup named Parabeac. Please have the latest version of Android installed and configured prior to attendance. We will also provide a link to our github repository to make it easier to follow along with the workshop. Hope to see you all there. Best, Google Developer Group El Paso Chapter The link to the android content is here: https://github.com/gdg-el-paso/Android-Workshops Please have this downloaded prior to attending.
